message: How does plastic pollution affect marine ecosystems?
output: Climate change can lead to ocean acidification, coral bleaching, and disruption of marine food chains, impacting marine biodiversity. Measures to protect marine biodiversity include creating marine protected areas, reducing plastic pollution, and promoting sustainable fishing practices to preserve ocean ecosystems.
